item.comment:
Tony,
The following method is accessing the ThreadContext. Isn't this shared, and so require synchronized access?  Is it not possible when multiple threads are executing in this, they would overwrite the 'sid'?
For instance, consider the following steps:
1. Thread 1 executes the 'if(sid==null)' line (and has to give up the CPU)
2. Thread 2 executes the 'if(sid==null)' line (and has to give up the CPU)
3. Thread 1 continues to create a new 'sid', and put it in the ThreadContext
4. Thread 2 continues now, has no way of knowing that the 'sid' is no longer null, so proceeds to get a new 'sid', replacing the one fetched by Thread 1,in the ThreadContext.
5.If Thread 1 at this point executes the api the reference to which was obtained with an older 'sid', wouldn't it cause problems?
Also, why is there is no logout anywhere?
