MSA requires the ability to make 2 calls in order to identify the insurable object. This is primarily an issue for commercial auto where dozens or even hundreds of vehicles can exist on a policy. In this case, they want the user to use the existing policy search to select the policy, and then have CC perform another call to retrieve the valid VINs on the policy and some descriptive information. The user would then select the VIN and coverage information for that vehicle would be retrieved.
Current work arounds require the user to enter the VIN as part of the initial search criteria, but it is very unlikely this information will be available during FNOL. The preferable solution would generalize the second call such that vehicles, locations, or any covered item could be searched.
This is a high priority requirement at MSA for the auto release, and is scheduled to be worked on in June, 06.
